source: http://According to Article 39 of NIOC Transaction Bylaw, the government award contracts and licenses via limited biding rounds for contracts over IIR 200,000,000.00 based on the Iran Biding Law. For contracts up to 200,000,000.00, the government award license and contracts via price inquiry process. Moreover, according to Article 11 of Ministry of Petroleum Discretion and Duties Law, granting and execution of exploration and development projects of shared oil fields is exempted from Iran Biding Law.
